creenFromWeb?topicID=37.topic&index=6>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: At what age should a juvinile be tried as an adult</span><hr size=1> Legal drinking age here is 18 and we laugh at all the 18 yr old americans that come and just get smashed beyond recognition.<br>
<br>
We have 18 yr old drunks, but not more than you have 21 yr old drunks. But drinking alcohol has little to nothing to do with you beeing responsible or not, I remember drinking legaly at 15 in Spain and none were drunk. The more you taboo something, the more kids will abuse it.<br>
<br>
I'd Say the crime should dictate the trial level, no sens in trying a 14 yr old in adult court for theft cause his friends dared him to grab that car stereo, However they sure are big enough to know murder is wrong no matter what peer pressure they are under.<br>
<br>
