</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#2F2F4F><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub79.ezboard.com/umaddiefaye.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Maddie Faye</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FFFFFF>(6/19/02 11:40:54 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub79.ezboard.com/finfinitusvindicatfrm9.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=37.topic&index=9>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://www.fallenalliance.org/screenshots/downwpst.gif  WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: At what age should a juvinile be tried as an adult</span><hr size=1> Umberlie, some very interesitng points.<br>
<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i>  being in the military DOES mean you are one of the major contributors to the stability and safety of our society. </i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--><br>
<br>
More than a volunteer Fireman in a small town? <p><a href=http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=18533>Sister Maddie Faye</a></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#666699><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub79.ezboard.com/umorkenlar.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Morkenlar</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Councilman</span><br> <font color=#FFFFFF>(6/19/02 2:28:15 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub79.ezboard.com/finfinitusvindicatfrm9.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=37.topic&index=10>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: At what age should a juvinile be tried as an adult</span><hr size=1> Well, since I grew up in a small town, I'd have to say YES, Maddie.  &quot;Volunteer firemen&quot; can mean anything from someone you carries the gatorade to the firement, to someone who presses a button on the truck, to someone who charges in to a raging inferno to say a dozen infants.  Very large range there, but in general, they don't usually take risky actions.<br>
<br>
People in the military, however, get sent to war.  I don't think its a fair comparison at all.  Easy comparison - take extreme cases.  Compare the most heroic fireman of all time, to the greatest war hero of all time.  Who made the most difference?<br>
  <br>
<br>
 <p></br>

<img src=http://home.attbi.com/~shay01/morksiggy.gif
>


</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#2F2F4F><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub79.ezboard.com/udelarawyldheart.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Delara Wyldheart</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://delarawyldheart.freeservers.com/images/starblink.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Membership Coordinator</span><br> <font color=#FFFFFF>(6/20/02 7:59:35 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub79.ezboard.com/finfinitusvindicatfrm9.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=37.topic&index=11>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://delarawyldheart.freeservers.com/images/yinyang.gif WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: At what age should a juvinile be tried as an adult</span><hr size=1> Who made the most difference to whom?<br>
<br>
To the mother who will get to watch her baby grow up after being rescued from that blazing inferno... the fireman.<br>
<br>
To the mother whos son's live was saved because a brave soldier put him self at risk because he would not leave a fallen comrad... the war hero.<br>
<br>
As for what age a person should be tried as an adult should depend on the individual...some 12 year olds are as mature as some 18-21 year olds, and I have seen some 30 year olds I wouldn't trust outside the confines of their play yards.<br>
<br>
