</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#2F2F4F><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub79.ezboard.com/uumberliefa.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Umberlie FA</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FFFFFF>(6/20/02 12:54:56 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub79.ezboard.com/finfinitusvindicatfrm9.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=37.topic&index=13>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: At what age should a juvinile be tried as an adult</span><hr size=1> Well Mork you've compared the 2 heroes, how bout we compare the guy that brings gatorade to the Firemen with the soldier on dish washing duty in a station in middle of the desert in Nevada.<br>
<br>
The are heroes in all instances of life, the beggar who jumps passed a bus to save the kid running after his ball, the old man who convinces a young woman that suicide is not the way to go, the fireman charging into the fire to save people, the war heroe putting himself in danger for his country ... Then again again, you also have the idiots and the clueless that sometimes make it as polititians, cops, firemen, and militaries. <br>
<br>
Beeing in the army means little to me. What you do while in the army is what counts. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#666699><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub79.ezboard.com/uvizco.showPublicProfile?language=EN>vizco</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FFFFFF>(6/20/02 2:28:53 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub79.ezboard.com/finfinitusvindicatfrm9.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=37.topic&index=14>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://www.harmonyofsouls.org/pics/hosicon_flag.gif WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: At what age should a juvinile be tried as an adult</span><hr size=1> The part of the brain that controls impulse and planning doesn't mature until the mid-20s.<br>
